===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[κοινός]]''' "shared, common, public, general, ordinary, usual"

===Noun===
'''Koine'''
# A [[dialect]] of the [[Greek]] [[language]] that developed and [[flourish|flourished]] between 300 BC and AD 300 (the time of the [[Roman Empire]]) and from which [[Modern Greek]] [[descended]]. It was based on the [[Attic]] and [[Ionian]] dialects.

